[[!meta title="Numerous security holes in Tails 3.4"]]
[[!pagetemplate template="news.tmpl"]]

[[!tag security/fixed]]

Several security holes that affect Tails 3.4 are now fixed in Tails 3.5.

We **strongly** encourage you to
[[upgrade to Tails 3.5|news/version_3.5]] as soon as possible.

- Tor Browser:
  [MSFA 2018-03](https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/security/advisories/mfsa2018-03/)
- amd64-microcode: [[!cve CVE-2017-5715]]
- thunderbird: [[!debsa2017 4075]], [[!debsa2017 4061]]
- libxml2: [[!debsa2018 4086]]
- gdk-pixbuf: [[!debsa2018 4088]]
- bind9: [[!debsa2018 4089]]
